This is what the job entails. \n< Ochre >
A trade partner for a certain item will arrive soon. \n< Ochre >
We and those guys are tense...in fact, we can say
that we are in a hostile relationship. \n< Ochre >
However, precisely because of such a relationship, the
profit in business is huge. \n< Ochre >
Taboos can bring in money. However, we must never let
our guard down. \n< Ochre >
We are both calculating the timing to cut each other.
Or perhaps waiting for the timing when the other party
makes a move. \n< Ochre >
I have to betray before being betrayed. But the deal
is sweet. I want to keep going until the very end. \n< Ochre >
Here, a state of balance is born. A precarious
balance, you know? \n< Ochre >
What should I do? \n< Serena >
I want you to facilitate the transaction. No, I'm not
saying you have to talk. \n< Ochre >
Be silent instead. Don't talk. Don't do anything
unnecessary. \n< Ochre >
When we do the transaction, we and they will face
each other. You walk out of our line, give them the
goods, receive the money, and come back. Easy, right? \n< Ochre >
In case something happens, it means being the first
to die. \n< Serena >
Hehehe... Well, don't take it so badly. Your prideful
armor should be able to handle it, right? \n< Ochre >
Perhaps. \n< Serena >
Hmph, you're not cute, kid. \n< Ochre >
Oh, you've arrived. Do your best, alright? \n< Ochre >

So they're gone. They even took the gold bars with
them perfectly. \n< Serena >
Hey, you. Kid... \n< Ochre >
Ah, Lord Ochre. You're still alive. This is an
unexpected turn of events. \n< Serena >
What...did you say!? \n< Ochre >
I'm going to ruin the deal! The money will be left
behind! The women have escaped! \n< Ochre >
Do you understand? This is a huge loss... We'll be
erased by the guild... No, something even worse will
happen.  \n< Ochre >
I'm sorry. I lost my temper and acted impulsively. I
will report this to the Guild and take responsibility
for my actions. \n< Serena >
Of course! You guys. Catch this brat! \n< Ochre >
Shit...this is a huge failure...even if I blame it on
the kid, will the guild let me get away with it? Damn
it, damn it...! \n< Ochre >
At least capture this brat... \n< Ochre >
They want us to go quietly and be taken away. It's
best for us not to cause any trouble. \n< Serena >
You must have seen the battle just now. I still have
plenty of energy left. \n< Serena >
Damn it! It's the guild! Let's take them! \n< Ochre >
Ah! Shut up! Is that all you can say?! Just that?!  \n< Ochre >
...Well then. For now, we can say that the first stage
has been a success. \n< Serena >
Let's pray that Lady Cecilia leads us well from here. \n< Serena >
